**who —** SUPER METROID — the single-game deep-dive — the SNES masterpiece (parent: MET)

**what —** Super Metroid — the lonely, interconnected SNES world you explore in silence: the cold open on Ceres, the descent through Zebes by ability-gated doors, the four Space Pirate lords and the brain wired to the planet, the gentle animals who teach you, and a baby's sacrifice.

**where —** Ceres Space Colony and the rebuilt planet Zebes — Crateria, Brinstar, Norfair, Maridia, the Wrecked Ship, Tourian; the SNES masterpiece, the third game  Framework inputs: Super Metroid; Ceres; Zebes; the baby Metroid; Mother Brain; the Chozo; the Power Suit  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)

**why —** A lone hunter pursues the stolen baby Metroid back into a living fortress-world, maps it alone, and is saved at the end by the very creature she was sent to destroy.

**how —** Crystallized from Super Metroid (Nintendo, SNES 1994) — the third Metroid game.

**◌ the mythos —** A lone hunter pursues the stolen baby Metroid back into a living fortress-world, maps it alone, and is saved at the end by the very creature she was sent to destroy. Routinely named among the greatest games ever made — and the one whose silent map taught a genre to be a key to itself.

**the moniker —** ⟦SUPER METROID:SMT:e6903a⟧ · spoken *nax-pheix-xeth*

**the seal —** Pursue the stolen hatchling down into Zebes alone — and at the bottom, the menace you came to end gives its life to save you.

